-- Indian shares bounce back after 3 days of losses
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 06:13AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 9 (Reuters) - Indian shares snapped a three-day losing streak on Thursday as hopes the U.S. Federal Reserve would not rush into raising interest rates sparked a rally in global markets and boosted blue-chips such as ICICI Bank <ICBK.NS>.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 1.49 percent higher at 26,637.28, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended 1.5 percent stronger at 7,960.55.